# Generic template for adding another gateway beyond the two this
# environment ships pre-filled (.env.gateway.litellm / .env.gateway.portkey
# — see those for two complete, filled-in examples pointing at this repo's
# own llm-gateways environment). Copy this file to .env.gateway.<name> —
# <name> becomes what you pass to scripts/point-to-gateway.sh, or pick
# from its no-argument picker — and fill in both values below. See the
# README's "Pointing Claude CLI at a Gateway" section for the full
# picture.
#
# This file itself is the template, not a live config — the same role
# .env.example plays for .env. It's excluded from
# scripts/point-to-gateway.sh's own picker (matched by the literal
# "example" suffix, same as .env.example itself is never treated as a
# real .env anywhere in this repo) and is meant to always stay free of
# real credentials — unlike the .env.gateway.<name> copies you make from
# it, which backup.sh's own per-environment archive step doesn't include
# (it only ever archives the literal .env, never .env.gateway.*) —
# deliberately, once you've filled one in for real.

# Base URL Claude Code should send requests to instead of
# api.anthropic.com. Must speak the Anthropic Messages API shape
# specifically — not a generic OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions
# endpoint, a different request/response format than what most
# self-hosted gateways expose by default. Confirm whatever you're
# pointing this at actually speaks that shape before relying on it — see
# the README section referenced above for why this isn't something this
# repo can verify for you in advance.
# Format: A URL.
ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=

# Bearer credential for the endpoint above.
# Format: A token string.
ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=
